🔹 Step 2: Build the Docker Image
Open your terminal or command prompt in the flask-registration folder and run:

bash
Copy
Edit



docker build -t flask-registration-app .


  
🛠️ What this does:

-t flask-registration-app names your image.

. means Dockerfile is in the current directory.

🔹 Step 3: Run the Docker Container
bash
Copy
Edit


docker run -p 5000:5000 flask-registration-app



  
🔁 This maps your local port 5000 to the container's port 5000.

🔹 Step 4: Open in Browser
Visit:


👉 http://localhost:5000

You’ll see the registration form. Try entering a name and email.
